ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a class that you don't realize that you need it until you have taken it.
EEB 545 teaches you how to think and act ethically in a research environment. This is vital for maintaining high ethical standards in our field. The course itself is interesting and well structured.
This course is about how to be an ethical, professional member of the academic community. I would recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course provided me with the tools to think through ethical problems in scientific research and the general research environment. I will use these skills for the entirety of my career.
I am more aware of the issues - ethical, personal, and professional - I will face throughout grad school and my career, and I have a better sense of how to respond to them.
